In recent years, various types of CNMs, including G and its derivatives, CNTs, carbon nanofibers (CNFs), carbon nanowires (CNWs), fullerene, graphene QDs (GQDs), with different characteristics, morphologies, and structures have been used to design and develop bio−/nano-sensors (Fig. 3
                           ). In the next sections, recent advances in various CNMs-based bio−/nano-sensors for ANBr detection have been described in more detail (Tables 2 and 3

                           ).
